---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Web Design for Hair Salons | FisherDigital"
  description="Websites for hair salons and barbers across the UK. Showcase your work, take bookings online, and stop relying on Instagram alone to fill your appointment book."
  schemaType="niche"
  niche="Hair Salons"
  nicheDescription="Professional websites, online booking, and AI chatbots built specifically for hair salons and barber shops in the UK."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section-light py-(--spacing-section)">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <span class="label block mb-4">Web design for hair salons</span>
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-heading font-600 tracking-tight mb-6">
          Instagram gets the likes.<br />
          <span class="text-accent">Your website gets the bookings.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-light-text-secondary)] max-w-xl mb-10 leading-relaxed">
          Your Instagram is full of beautiful transformations. But Instagram doesn't show up when someone Googles "hair salon near me." A proper website does. It shows your work, your prices, and lets people book without sending a DM and waiting hours for a reply.
        </p>
        <a href="/#contact" data-hover
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 bg-accent text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-sm font-600 hover:bg-accent-hover transition-all shadow-lg shadow-accent/20 hover:shadow-accent/40">
          Book a free call
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pain Points -->
  <section class="bg-white py-(--spacing-section)">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <span class="label block mb-4">The problem</span>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-600 tracking-tight">
          Why full chairs start with your website.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <!-- Pain 1 -->
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-[var(--color-border)] p-8 bg-[var(--color-surface-light)]">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-accent" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M21 21l-6-6m2-5a7 7 0 11-14 0 7 7 0 0114 0z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-600 mb-3">Google can't find your salon</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            When someone new to the area searches "hairdresser in [your town]," they get Google results. Not Instagram results. If you don't have a website, you don't exist to Google. That's clients walking straight past your door to the salon that does show up.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pain 2 -->
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-[var(--color-border)] p-8 bg-[var(--color-surface-light)]">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-accent" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M8 12h.01M12 12h.01M16 12h.01M21 12c0 4.418-4.03 8-9 8a9.863 9.863 0 01-4.255-.949L3 20l1.395-3.72C3.512 15.042 3 13.574 3 12c0-4.418 4.03-8 9-8s9 3.582 9 8z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-600 mb-3">DM booking is slow and messy</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            You're mid-cut and a DM comes in asking about availability. Then three more. By the time you check at 8pm, two of them have already booked elsewhere. DMs don't scale. A booking form works while you're busy with clients.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pain 3 -->
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-[var(--color-border)] p-8 bg-[var(--color-surface-light)]">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-accent" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M9 5H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2h-2M9 5a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2M9 5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-600 mb-3">No price list means wasted consultations</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            People want to know ballpark prices before they commit. Without a clear price list online, you end up fielding the same "how much for a balayage?" message twenty times a week. Or worse, they assume you're expensive and never ask at all.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What We Build -->
  <section class="section-light py-(--spacing-section)">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <span class="label block mb-4">What you get</span>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-600 tracking-tight mb-12">
          Your salon's best look, online.
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            <div>
              <p class="font-600 text-[var(--color-light-text)] mb-1">Portfolio gallery fed from your Instagram</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-light-text-secondary)]">Your best before-and-afters, colour work, and styling shots displayed in a proper gallery. Organised by service type so clients can see exactly the kind of work they're booking.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            <div>
              <p class="font-600 text-[var(--color-light-text)] mb-1">Full price list and service menu</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-light-text-secondary)]">Cuts, colours, treatments, styling, extensions. All listed with prices and approximate times. Clients know what to expect before they book. Fewer "how much?" messages for you.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            <div>
              <p class="font-600 text-[var(--color-light-text)] mb-1">Online booking that fills quiet days</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-light-text-secondary)]">Clients pick a stylist, a service, and a time slot. Works at midnight, works on a Sunday. You wake up Monday with a full book instead of an empty one.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            <div>
              <p class="font-600 text-[var(--color-light-text)] mb-1">Meet the team section</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-light-text-secondary)]">Photos and bios for every stylist. Clients pick who they want based on specialisms and personality. It makes the booking feel personal before they've set foot in the salon.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-white py-(--spacing-section)">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-600 tracking-tight mb-6">
        See what we build for salons.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] max-w-xl mx-auto mb-10">
        We've built demo sites for businesses like yours. Take a look at our portfolio, then book a free call to talk about what your salon needs.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-5">
        <a href="/#portfolio" data-hover
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 bg-accent text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-sm font-600 hover:bg-accent-hover transition-all shadow-lg shadow-accent/20 hover:shadow-accent/40">
          See our portfolio
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/#contact" data-hover
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-sm font-500 border border-[var(--color-border-light)] hover:border-accent hover:text-accent transition-all">
          Book a free call
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
